        <c02 level="item" id="d1e197">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Horace Greeley</persname>to 
                  <persname>Henry David Thoreau</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1848 May 17</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>2 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Discusses business, money due from 
                  <persname>George Rex Graham</persname>for published
                  articles, fees for " 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Maine Woods</bibref>" and " 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Carlyle</bibref>, " and suggestions for
                  future articles.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e228">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Horace Greeley</persname>to 
                  <persname>Henry David Thoreau</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1848 May 25</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>2 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Accompanies check for " 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Maine Woods</bibref>"; requests more article;
                  mentions publication of Thoreau's letter in a
                  newspaper and criticizes young men unwilling to
                  work.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e253">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Horace Greeley</persname>to 
                  <persname>Henry David Thoreau</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1852 Apr 13</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>2 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Requests article on 
                  <persname>Ralph Waldo Emerson</persname>. ]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e278">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Horace Greeley</persname>to 
                  <persname>Henry David Thoreau</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1854 Mar 6</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>3 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Asks him to assemble several articles for which
                  Greeley will try to find a publisher.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e300">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Horace Greeley</persname>to Dr.
                  Polney</unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1859 Mar 4</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>1 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Requests meeting to review what 
                  <persname>Horace Greeley</persname>has written about
                  the 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">New American Cyclopaedia</bibref>. ]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
